    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-22T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.50/3</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-22T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1917, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 4.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5736. Your 4467, February 20, 7 p.m., was immediately made known personally to
                    Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>. He remarked that one
                    difficulty in the way of supplies reaching Greece was the enemy submarines in
                    the Mediterranean. He said that other aspects of the subject were receiving
                    Government attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
